{
  "texts": [
    "Although the eRASS1 catalogues presented here are complete (i.e.",
    "includes also sources in the SEP region), an optimized SEP catalogue will be presented in Liu et al. (2024), where a more sophisticated data processing and source detection optimized for crowded regions with deep (and spatially variable) exposure will be introduced.",
    "Consistency checks with external catalogues Comparison with XMM source fluxesBefore eRASS1, the previous best all-sky X-ray catalogue was provided by the ROSAT all-sky survey (2RXS: Boller et al. 2016).",
    "In terms of pure source numbers, the largest X-ray catalogue previous to eRASS1 is the XMM-Newton serendipitous catalogue (4XMM: Rosen et al. 2016; Webb et al.",
    "Covering only a small fraction of the sky, 4XMM has a similar resolution to eROSITA and generally deeper exposure than eRASS1."
  ]
}